A28. Implement a security solution of your choice and put it on your GitHub
This program is designed to improve basic security by ensuring that users create strong passwords. 
Weak passwords are one of the most common causes of security breaches. 
Therefore, this program checks the strength of a password and only accepts it if it meets specific security requirements.

The program is written in Python and uses a function to evaluate whether a password is strong or weak. It continuously prompts the user to enter a password until it satisfies all required conditions.

The password must meet the following criteria:

1. At least 8 characters long
2. Contains at least one uppercase letter
3. Contains at least one lowercase letter
4. Contains at least one number
5. Contains at least one special character

If the password does not meet these conditions, the program asks the user to try again.
This program also prevent code injection by not using function like eval() or exec(). 
The input function also read as string so it will not be execute.
